{
  "stem": "11964.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And most of all, how will we be able, I mean the three sisters, to continue as the nucleus of our family and possibly get in touch with other families that we have that I knew we had, at least in Israel?",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So Radomsko was a fiasco.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We couldn't find anybody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We couldn't think of staying there longer than we had to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we really promised ourselves never to step foot in Radomsko any longer, because we really encountered such hostility.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went to Warsaw, and I said to you, we were able to find a shelter, and then I got a job in the Ministry of Education in the government.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sister got a job also.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And slowly but surely, many of the people we knew who were a little bit on the left side, who would rather escape to Russia-- and many people escaped the Germans going to Russia-- would return.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many returned, and many got good positions in the government.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And many just returned.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we established a little bit of a community of those people whom we knew from Radomsko, and we would communicate with each other.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the very curious thing that happened is that, notwithstanding the fact that we were liberated, and that we were in Poland, and that was our country, we were told not to reveal that we are Jewish when we got the jobs in the government.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And mind you, I had to still function under my assumed false name, and so did my older sister.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we decided that this is something we could not endure anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A very strange coincidence happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When my younger sister was in the convent, she had befriended one girl.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
